<paragraph blockId="53.[151,1437,151,536]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,323,151,176]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Length ratio of tergites I, II, 
<date box="[648,776,151,176]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
III and IV 
<number box="[766,776,152,176]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" value="1.0">1</number>
</date>
: 
<number box="[780,820,152,176]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" value="4.1">4.1</number>
:2.0: 
<number box="[871,911,152,176]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" value="1.4">1.4</number>
. Tergites shiny brown, tergite III with a yellow subanterior fascia, its width about 
<number box="[549,559,188,212]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[570,584,188,212]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" value="3.0">3</number>
of the tergite length, the pile of tergites pale, short, adpressed, with some brown pile on posterior 
<number box="[430,440,224,248]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[450,465,224,248]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" value="2.0">2</number>
of tergite; tergite I with an oblique row of 
<number box="[969,1011,224,248]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4</number>
pale setae laterally; sternite IV (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 33" captionStartId="52.[151,250,1947,1969]" captionTargetBox="[181,1386,917,1879]" captionTargetId="figure@52.[175,1397,914,1882]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="FIGURE 33. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) pusilla sp. n. (holotype). A. Posterior part of sternite IV, ventral view. B. Genitalia, lateral view. C. Right surstylus, lateral view. D. Left surstylus, lateral view. Scale 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/288429/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,179,260,284]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" value="33.0">33</number>
</figureCitation>
A) brownish, the posterior part paler yellowish, the pile pale; sternites VI–VIII black, the pile short and pale. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,268,295,320]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Genitalia,</emphasis>
<figureCitation box="[278,363,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 33" captionStartId="52.[151,250,1947,1969]" captionTargetBox="[181,1386,917,1879]" captionTargetId="figure@52.[175,1397,914,1882]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="FIGURE 33. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) pusilla sp. n. (holotype). A. Posterior part of sternite IV, ventral view. B. Genitalia, lateral view. C. Right surstylus, lateral view. D. Left surstylus, lateral view. Scale 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/288429/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
Figs 
<number box="[335,363,296,320]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" value="33.0">33</number>
</figureCitation>
B–D. Note the slightly modified cercus and the asymmetrical surstyli. The superior lobes are symmetrical. Sternite IX is asymmetrical. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[624,751,332,357]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">FEMALE.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
